itemDescription: Irish baronet and cricket player of England (1861-1948)

wikipedia_page.main: Sir Timothy Carew O'Brien, 3rd Baronet (5 November 1861 – 9 December 1948) was an Irish baronet who played cricket for England in five Test matches.

response: * Sir Tim O'Brien, 3rd Baronet (1861–1948), Irish-born cricketer

link_mentions.page: List of cricketers who were knighted
response: *Tim O'Brien inherited his father's baronetcy, becoming Sir Tim O'Brien, 3rd Baronet, of Merrion Square and Boris-in-Ossory, in the Baronetage of the United Kingdom.
*9 December – Sir Tim O'Brien, 3rd Baronet, cricketer (born 1861).
